creator: Ned Wayburn
description:
LibriVox recording of The Art of Stage Dancing by Ned Wayburn.

Read in English by Jill Janovetz; Viglione; Ramon Escamilla; Jewel Raquel; MaryAnn; Cynthia Moyer; Pamela Krantz; ashleighjane; rookieblue; Marmalade Hanna; Suebee; PDyer; Kristin Gjerløw; Availle; Peter Makus; Anna Simon

Ned Wayburn, a popular and outstanding choreographer of the early 1900's, writes about the different styles and requirements of dancing and his way of teaching it.

For further information, including links to online text, reader information, RSS feeds, CD cover or other formats (if available), please go to the LibriVox catalog page for this recording.

For more free audio books or to become a volunteer reader, visit LibriVox.org.
